      <akn:section eId="sec_28_5003">
        <akn:num>28-5003</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Civil relief; damages.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-5003_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-5003_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>At the request of any party to an action brought pursuant to this section, the court may, in its discretion, conduct all legal proceedings in such a way as to protect the secrecy and security of the computer, computer network, computer data, computer program, and computer software involved to prevent possible recurrence of the same or similar act by another person and to protect any trade secrets of any party.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-5003_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-5003_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Attorney General of the District of Columbia may enforce the provisions of this chapter pursuant to authority granted in ยง 28-3909.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
